The task force is led by Dr. David Sinclair, a brilliant scientist who is also a single father. Sinclair, having been a recipient of the type of mug in question was therefore also a victim of the incident and was driven to finding the answer to the question of why he was not number one dad, but dad number one million seven hundred and fifty eight thousand two hundred and forty one. 

Sinclair's team was able to track the source of the anomaly to a small town in the United States. An ad hoc research facility was established and the team began their research by compiling a list of all of the fathers in town that the incident had affected. Being a small town, they quickly were able to interview all of the men. However, for months they still had still not formed a hypothesis until one day when Dr. Sinclair made a breakthrough. 

He was able to deduce that the anomaly was not a result of the men's actions, but rather the actions of their children. It turns out that the largest conspiracy ever had taken place and that those who had conspired where the all of the children that had given their fathers at one point a "#1 Dad" mug. They had resolved to input all of the information about their dads into a predetermined algorithm that would collate the dads by who was best. They then had resolved to replace the #1 Dad" mugs at the same time. Thus, Task Force Papa One was dissolved having solved the mystery and each father knew how good of a father he really was. In the end, the children of the men posited that by knowing this information, all fathers would strive better to be better dads.
